==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mytilotoxine
<hw>Myt`i*lo*tox"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mytilus</ets> + <ets>toxic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A poisonous base (leucomaine) found in the common
mussel. It either causes paralysis of the muscles, or gives rise to
convulsions, including death by an accumulation of carbonic acid in the
blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mytilus</ent>⟦br⟧
